Lunarpine had crossed through enemy territory, when he caught the 
explosion. "Poor sparks" he thought as he flew on. his transport pod 
was making good time. He was now flying over the ocean, the view 
wasn't much through the clouds but good weather was on his side. he 
approached Europe at top speed, it wouldn't be long now until he 
found what he was looking for.


Meanwhile in Norway the two new bots were prepareing for the return 
of Foxfingers with the dna they required.

"Are the machines ready for the first trial run?" the Bot resembling 
a bat asked

"Almost father" the Hawkbot replied, "We need more material for the 
test."

"I may have to send you out if Foxfingers fails, would you like 
that?" the first said, a small smile on his lips, he already knew the 
answer but he had to make it her decision. 

"You know I would father, it's been to long since I got to spread my 
wings." the female replied finding a reasonable excuse to let her go.

"Then go my Ladybird but don't forget about our mission" he  
exclaimed. It bothered him to allow her access to this big world but 
he cared for her to much to deny her such luxuries.

"Yes my father, Till All Are One." with those words she became 
airborne. she transformed to a three eyed hawk, spread her wings and 
flew like a newborne bird spreading it's wings for the first time.
